  "prompt": "How do I recover my Facebook account password without a recovery email or phone number?",
  "response": "If you\u2019re trying to recover your Facebook account without access to a recovery email or phone number, you can try the following steps:\n\n1. **Go to the Facebook Login Page**: Visit the Facebook login page and click on \u201cForgot password?\u201d.\n\n2. **Identify Your Account**: Enter your username, full name, or the name of a friend in the search bar. Click \"Search\" to find your account.\n\n3. **Choose Recovery Option**: If you don\u2019t have access to the email or phone number listed, look for the option that says \"No longer have access to these?\" or similar. This will initiate a process to help you regain access to your account.\n\n4. **Identify Friends**: Facebook may ask you to identify friends based on their photos. Follow the prompts to answer correctly.\n\n5. **Answer Security Questions**: If you have set up security questions, you may be presented with them. Provide the correct answers.\n\n6. **Identity Verification**: If you\u2019re unable to recover the account through the above methods, Facebook may allow you to verify your identity using a government-issued ID. Follow the prompts to upload any required documents.\n\n7. **Support Options**: If you still cannot recover your account, you may need to visit the Facebook Help Center. Look for options such as \u201cGet help\u201d or \u201cReport a login issue\u201d. \n\n8. **Wait for Response**: After you submit your identity verification or appeal, wait for Facebook\u2019s response. They will guide you on the next steps.\n\n9. **Create a New Account**: If all else fails and you cannot recover your account, consider creating a new Facebook account.\n\nRemember to keep your new account information secure and update your recovery options to avoid future issues.",
